To include or re-include Git template content into your repository do one of:

- Set the "init.templatedir" to the git_template directory path, e.g.
  git config --global init.templatedir '~/.git_template'

  You only need to do this once.

  Run `git init` on any existing repositories to apply the template content,
  future repos will automatically include it.

- Include the "--template" option pointing to the git_template directory path
  when you run git clone or init.
